communication as selection from a set of possible symbols
bit is a measure of surprise

pictogram - a symbol that represents a physical object, like water or a liton
ideogram - represent a mental concept, like 'middle'

the letters of alphabet took their forms mostly from pictograms, e.g. 'm' took its form from the pictogram that stands for water.

descreet source code is when you have a finite set of posible symbols to choose from
